Class FSSubsetMutationPipeline

  • java.lang.Object
    • ec.BreedingSource
      • ec.BreedingPipeline
        • ristretto.problem.fs.subset.breed.FSSubsetMutationPipeline
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ec.Prototype, ec.Setup, ec.steadystate.SteadyStateBSourceForm, ec.util.RandomChoiceChooserD, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class FSSubsetMutationPipeline
extends ec.BreedingPipeline
    FSSubsetMutationPipeline is a BreedingPipeline which implements a simple default Mutation for FSSubsetIndividual. Normally it takes an individual and returns a mutated child individual. FSSubsetMutationPipeline works by calling FSSubsetIndividual.defaultMutate(ec.EvolutionState, int) on the parent individual. It has been adapted from the original ECJ's VectorMutationPipeline.java (Copyright 2006 by Sean Luke under the AFL v. 3.0) to grab and produce FSSubsetIndividuals.

    Typical Number of Individuals Produced Per produce(...) call
    (however many its source produces)

    Number of Sources

    Default Base
    fs-subset.mutate (not that it matters)
